spans.text: At Mary's Tomb , ( sad , sacred Place ! )
Records her Deeds repeat : Ages to come , and Men unborn Shall bless her Name , and sigh her Fate
dismiss his Woes , Reflecting on his fair Renown
Them Thy auspicious Light , Great Sun
Those Clouds , which keep Thee from our Sight
for William's Life , That Mary's Fate She dare not mourn
her Strength in Thee be safe : And let Her weep
She pulls her Helmet over her Eyes , Lest He should see the falling Tear
Where Death with all his Darts is seen
If Her Regrets should waken Thine
If Her Regrets should waken Thine
that Right , For which Their pious Parents fell
How Heroes rise , how Patriots set
forget Thy own : New Toils endure ; new Conquest give
Receives it's Forms , Thy Virtues roll : From Mary's Glory , Angels trace The Beauty of her Partner's Soul
it's Forms , Thy Virtues roll : From Mary's Glory , Angels trace The Beauty of her Partner's Soul
does it's Heaven decree To Heroes
